## Residents Table Structure

Here's the complete schema for the `residents` table in the Sentrina database:

### Table Definition (src/backend/migrations/sql/01-create-tables.sql:37)

| Column | Type | Constraints | Default |
|--------|------|-------------|---------|
| `id` | SERIAL | PRIMARY KEY | Auto-increment |
| `username` | VARCHAR(100) | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | - |
| `password_hash` | VARCHAR(255) | NULL allowed | - |
| `full_name` | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL | - |
| `lot_number` | VARCHAR(50) | NULL allowed | - |
| `block` | VARCHAR(50) | NULL allowed | - |
| `email` | VARCHAR(255) | NULL allowed | - |
| `phone` | VARCHAR(50) | NULL allowed | - |
| `profile_image` | TEXT | NULL allowed | - |
| `role` | VARCHAR(50) | - | 'homeowner' |
| `status` | VARCHAR(50) | - | 'active' |
| `date_registered` | DATE | - | CURRENT_DATE |
| `last_login` | TIMESTAMP | NULL allowed | - |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | - | CURRENT_TIMESTAMP |
| `updated_at` | TIMESTAMP | - | CURRENT_TIMESTAMP |

